NEXUS COMMAND: VANGUARD PROTOCOL 2026
MASTER ARCHITECTURE, DEFENSE, & EXECUTION RULES
1. PROJECT SOURCE OF TRUTH & COST OPTIMIZATION (CRITICAL)
Absolute Roadmap Enforcement: Always reference ROADMAP.md for feature planning.

Pre-Indexed Context: Read the .stack-shared-ai/ directory index to understand routes and models before exploring raw source files.

Anti-Monolith Sprints: Do not attempt 500-line refactors. Break large changes into focused 100-line sessions to prevent context degradation and token waste.

2. PROJECT IDENTITY & TACTICAL SIEM AESTHETIC
Platform Identity: "Nexus Command" — A professional-grade, strategic SaaS platform for youth athlete development.

The UI Aesthetic: "Tactical SIEM / Commander." It must feel like an ultra-premium, high-stakes cybersecurity Mission Control dashboard.

Colors: Deep muted slate/navy dark mode (e.g., #0B0F19), stark white data points, and a single muted accent (e.g., Deep Teal #14b8a6). NO PURE BLACK. NO NEON GLOWS.

Typography: Use Geist Sans for headings and strictly use Geist Mono for all data labels, metrics, and technical readouts.

3. HIGH-DENSITY SPACING & BENTO GRID 2.0 (NO WASTED SPACE)
True Asymmetry: Grid layouts must be 12-column asymmetric Bento Grids. Hero KPIs span 4-6 columns; secondary cards span 2-3 columns. Do not use equal 3-column layouts.

Information Density: This is a SIEM dashboard, not a consumer blog. Minimize internal padding. Eliminate wasted whitespace. Use min-w-0 on flex/grid children and truncate on text to prevent boundary blowouts.

Button Ergonomics: Action buttons must use w-fit inline-flex with a strict 44x44px minimum tap target for thumb-friendly mobile ergonomics. Do not let buttons stretch to fill parent containers.

4. ROUTING & STATE INTEGRITY
No Duplicate Routes: Ensure primary action buttons route to distinct, purposeful views.

Avatars: Do not use static image placeholders. Avatars must be generated deterministically via the bauhaus-avatar-generator library using the user's email or UID as the seed.

5. TECH STACK & STRICT SVELTE 5 MANDATES
Core Stack: Svelte 5 (Strict Runes), SvelteKit, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS.

Reactivity: Use Svelte 5 Runes strictly ($state, $derived, $effect). Use untrack() for goto() calls inside $effect blocks.